name: creative_material_mode
description: The strategy that your creatives will be delivered. Note: When you choose automated ad, your creative materials will automatically be combined for delivery. Tiktok Ads' smart optimization algorithm is applied and will be used to achieve the best ad performance during delivery. Enum values: CUSTOM(custom), DYNAMIC(automated)

name: audience_ids
description: A list of audience IDs

name: excluded_audience_ids
description: A list of excluded audience ID

name: audience_rule
description: Rules that specify your audience.

name: audience_type
description: App retargeting audience type. For enum values, see Enumeration - App Retargeting Audience Type.

name: location_ids
description: IDs of the locations that you want to target. Use Get locations to get available locations.

name: is_hfss
description: Whether the promoted product is HFSS foods (foods that are high in fat, salt, or sugar).

name: interest_category_ids
description: Interest classification. If the interest is specified, users that do not meet interest target will be excluded during delivery. Do not specify if you wish to target everyone. Use /tool/interest_category/ endpoint to get the complete list of interest categories.

name: interest_keyword_ids
description: IDs of interest keywords that you want to use to target audience. You can get interest keywords IDs by using the /tool/interest_keyword/recommend/ endpoint. For details, see Get interest keywords.

name: age_groups
description: Age groups you want to target. For enum values, see Enumeration - Age Group.

name: gender
description: Gender that you want to target. Enum values: GENDER_FEMALE,GENDER_MALE,GENDER_UNLIMITED

name: languages
description: Codes of the languages that you want to target. For the list of languages codes supported, see Enumeration - Language Code.

name: operating_systems
description: Device operating systems that you want to target. Only one value is allowed. Enum: ANDROID, IOS

name: network_types
description: Network types that you want to target. Default: unlimited. For enum values, see Enumeration - Connection Type.

name: device_price_ranges
description:
"Targeting device price range. 10000 means 1000+. The numbers must be in multiples of 50.
Important: The upper limit you set will be added by 50 and the resulting new number will be used as the actual upper limit for device targeting. The actual upper limit is shown in the ad group settings in TikTok Ads Manager. If you set and get the price range of [0, 250], it actually means [0, 300]."

name: min_android_version
description: Minimum Android version. For enum values, see Enumeration - Minimum Android Version.

name: min_ios_version
description: Audience minimum ios version. For enum values, see Enumeration - Minimum iOS Version.

name: ios14_targeting
description:
The iOS devices that you want to target.
Note: When campaign_type of the campaign is set as IOS14_CAMPAIGN, ios14_targeting is required in the request when creating an ad group and must be specified as IOS14_PLUS.

Enum values:
UNSET: The default value for ad groups that were created before the introduction of this field.
IOS14_MINUS: Devices with iOS 14.4 or earlier versions, which are not affected by the iOS 14 privacy update. This is the default value for ad groups that are created after the introduction of this field.
IOS14_PLUS: Devices with iOS 14.5 and above. The iOS 14 privacy update has been enforced in this group of devices. Specify this value if you want to create an iOS 14 campaign. Each iOS 14 campaign can have up to 2 active ad groups.

name: device_model_ids
description: List of device model IDs. For more details about device models, see Device Models.

name: household_income
description: Household income that you want to target. Enum values: TOP5(Top 5% of ZIP codes), TOP10(Top 10% of ZIP codes), TOP10_25(Top 10% -25% of ZIP codes), TOP25_50(Top 25% - 50% of ZIP codes).Note: household_income is an allowlist-only feature that is only available in US. If you would like to access it, please contact your TikTok representative.

name: spending_power
description: Spending power that you want to target. Enum values: ALL, HIGH. If it is set to HIGH, you can target high spending users who typically spend more on purchases than average users.Note: spending_power is an allowlist-only feature . If you would like to access it, please contact your TikTok representative.

name: budget_mode
description: Budget mode. If Campaign Budget Optimization is enabled, BUDGET_MODE_INFINITE will be returned. For more information about budget modes, see Budget Settings.

name: budget
description: Ad budget. Returns 0.0 when Campaign Budget Optimization (budget_optimize_on) is on.

name: scheduled_budget
description: Scheduled ad budget for next day. A value not equal to 0 means the scheduled budget is set and the value represents the budget; a value equals to 0 means the scheduled budget is not set.

name: schedule_type
description: The schedule type can be either SCHEDULE_START_END or SCHEDULE_FROM_NOW. If you choose SCHEDULE_START_END, you need to specify a start time and an end time. If you choose SCHEDULE_FROM_NOW, you only need to specify a start time.

name: schedule_start_time
description: Ad delivery start time (UTC+0). Format should be YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS

name: schedule_end_time
description: Ad delivery end time (UTC+0). Format should be YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS

name: dayparting
description:
"""Ad delivery arrangement, in the format of a string that consists of 48 x 7 characters. Each character is mapped to a 30-minute timeframe from Monday to Sunday. Each character can be set to either 0 or 1. 1 represents delivery in the 30-minute timeframe, and 0 stands for non-delivery in the 30-minute timeframe. The first character is mapped to 0:01-0:30 of Monday; The second character is mapped to 0:31-1:00 of Monday, and the last character represents 23:31-0:00 Sunday.Note
Not specified, all-0, or all-1 are considered as full-time delivery."

name: optimization_goal
description: The measurable results that you'd like to drive your ads with. For enum values, see Enumeration - Optimization Goal.

name: bid_display_mode
description: How you calculate and measure Cost per View.

name: cpv_video_duration
description:
Optimized video playback duration
Optional values include: SIX_SECONDS (video playback 6 seconds) and TWO_SECONDS (video playback 2 seconds)

name: conversion_window
description: The time frame when you would like a conversion to happen after a user clicks on or views your ad. Your ad delivery will be optimized using the conversion data during the time frame you select. This setting will not impact your attribution data. For enum values, ee Enumeration - Conversion Window.

name: pacing
description: You can choose between PACING_MODE_SMOOTH and PACING_MODE_FAST. For PACING_MODE_SMOOTH, the budget is allocated evenly within the scheduled time. PACING_MODE_FAST would consume budget and produce results as soon as possible. When Campaign Budget Optimization (budget_optimize_on) is on, your setting will be ignored and it will be set as PACING_MODE_SMOOTH. Otherwise, this field is required.

name: billing_event
description: Bid method. See Enumeration - Bid method for optional values.

name: skip_learning_phase
description: Whether to skip the learning stage.

name: bid_type
description:
Bidding strategy that determines how the system manages your cost per result, spends your budget, and how it delivers ads.
See Enumeration - Bidding Strategy.

name: bid_price
description: Bid price. The maximum cost per result you are willing to bid (for Bid Cap bidding strategy), or an average cost per result that you want to achieve (for Cost Cap bidding strategy).

name: conversion_bid_price
description: Where you can set a target cost per conversion for oCPM(Optimized Cost per Mille).

name: deep_bid_type
description: Bidding strategy for in-app events. For enum values and their decriptions, see Enumeration - Deep-level Bidding Strategy.

name: deep_cpa_bid
description: Specify bid price in this field after you've chosen a bidding strategy for in-app events, for example VO_MIN.

name: next_day_retention
description: Day 2 retention ratio. Formula: next_day_retention = conversion_bid_price/deep_cpa_bid. Value range is (0,1]. Only valid when placements is PLACEMENT_PANGLE and secondary_optimization_event is NEXT_DAY_OPEN.

name: secondary_status
description: Ad group status（secondary status). For enum values, see Enumeration - Ad Group Status - Secondary Status.

name: operation_status
description: Operational status. Enum: DISABLE (ad group is disabled), ENABLE (ad group is enabled), FROZEN (terminated and cannot be used again)

name: frequency
description:
"Frequency, together with frequency_schedule, controls how often people see your ad (only available for REACH ads).
The below conditions should be both met:1 <= frequency <= frequency_schedule * 3
1 <= frequency_schedule <=7
For example, frequency = 2 & frequency_schedule = 3 means ""show ads no more than twice every 3 day""."

name: frequency_schedule
description: Frequency_schedule, together with frequency, controls how often people see your ad (only available for REACH ads). See frequency fields for more.

name: statistic_type
description: Conversion bid statistic type, bid for EVERYTIME (Each Purchase)/ NONE (Unique Purchase)

name: carrier_ids
description: Carriers that you want to target. A carrier is valid only when the in_use field for the carrier is true. For detailed information, see get carriers.

name: video_download_disabled
description: Whether users can download your video ads on TikTok.

name: blocked_pangle_app_ids
description: Pangle app block list ID.

name: actions
description: A list of action category objects.

name: rf_purchased_type
description: Billing method of Reach & Frequency ad groups. For more details, see Enumeration - Reach & Frequency Buy Type. Returned when objective_type of the related campaign is RF_REACH.

name: purchased_impression
description: Impressions to be purchased. Returned when objective_type of the related campaign is RF_REACH.

name: purchased_reach
description: Purchased user reach. Returned when objective_type of the related campaign is RF_REACH.

name: rf_estimated_cpr
description: The estimated cost per mile reach. Returned when objective_type of the related campaign is RF_REACH.

name: rf_estimated_frequency
description: The estimated show frequency. Returned when objective_type of the related campaign is RF_REACH.

name: included_pangle_audience_package_ids
description: IDs of the Pangle audiences that you want to include. Valid only for Pangle placement. You can get audience IDs (package_id) by using the /pangle_audience_package/get/ endpoint. You need to set bind_type to INCLUDE. Do not specify this field and excluded_pangle_audience_package_ids at the same time.

name: excluded_pangle_audience_package_ids
description: IDs of the Pangle audiences that you want to exclude. Valid only for Pangle placement. You can get audience IDs (package_id) by using the /pangle_audience_package/get/ endpoint. You need to set bind_type to EXCLUDE. Do not specify this field and included_pangle_audience_package_ids at the same time.

name: is_new_structure
description: Whether the campaign is a new structure

name: catalog_id
description:
Catalog ID。
Return when the corresponding campaign objective_type is CATALOG_SALES.

name: product_set_id
description:
ProductSet ID of the catalog. 0 means selecting all product sets.
Return when the corresponding campaign objective_type is CATALOG_SALES.

name: catalog_authorized_bc_id
description: For catalogs in Business Center, this field returns the ID of the Business Center that a catalog belongs to.

name: included_custom_actions
description:
Catalog ad redirection contains conditions.
Return when the corresponding campaign objective_type is CATALOG_SALES.

name: excluded_custom_actions
description:
Catalog ad redirection does not contain conditions.
Return when the corresponding campaign objective_type is CATALOG_SALES.

name: shopping_ads_retargeting_type
description: The types of ad redirection in the catalog. Returned when the corresponding campaign objective_type is CATALOG_SALES/PRODUCT_SALES.

name: brand_safety_type
description:
Brand safety type. Enum values:THIRD_PARTY: Use a third-party brand safety solution. You also need to pass in a value to the brand_safety_partner field.
LIMITED_INVENTORY: Use TikTok's brand safety solution. Currently, the only supported safety level is Limited Inventory, which is a strict brand safety level. It would exclude all identifiable risky content. To get the countries and regions that your ads can be deployed to based on your brand safety settings, use the /tool/region/ endpoint.

name: brand_safety_partner
description: Brand safety partner. Available only when brand_safety_type is THIRD_PARTY. Enum values: IAS, OPEN_SLATE. To get the countries and regions that your ads can be deployed to based on your brand safety settings, use the /tool/region/ endpoint. You need to pass in the brand safety type and brand safety partner.

name: promotion_website_type
description: Instant page type in your ad group. Currently, the only supported type is TIKTOK_NATIVE_PAGE, which stands for TikTok instant pages. null means no instant pages are used in the ad group.

name: ios14_quota_type
description: Whether the campaign will be counted against the iOS 14 dedicated campaign quota. Enum: OCCUPIED, UNOCCUPIED. For non-R&F campaigns, when ios14_targeting is IOS14_PLUS, this field is automatically set to OCCUPIED.

name: roas_bid
description: ROAS goal for Value Optimization.

name: auto_targeting_enabled
description: Whether to enable automated targeting.

name: targeting_expansion
description: Settings about targeting expansion

name: adgroup_app_profile_page_state
description: Indicates whether the adgroup is using app profile page. Enum: INVALID, UNSET, ON, OFF.

name: shopping_ads_type
description: Shopping ads type. Enum values: UNSET, VIDEO(Video shopping ads),LIVE(Live shopping ads), CATALOG_LISTING_ADS

name: product_source
description: Enum values: UNSET ,CATALOG(Catalog), STORE (TikTok Shop or TikTok Storefront (third-party store)) .

name: feed_type
description: Feed type option. Enum values: STANDARD_FEED, TOP_FEED.

name: delivery_mode
description: The sequencing and schedule strategy for your ad display. Enum: OPTIMIZE(Optimized delivery that delivers ads to achieve the best performance)/STANDARD(Standard delivery that delivers ads in a random order)/SCHEDULE(Scheduled delivery that delivers ads according to the time period that you set)/SEQUENCE(Sequenced delivery that delivers ads in your expected order)

name: schedule_infos
description: Ad delivery information of R&F ad groups.

name: contextual_tag_ids
description: Contextual tag IDs. See Contextual targeting to learn more about how to use contextual targeting.

name: purchase_intention_keyword_ids
description: IDs of purchase intention keywords that you want to use to target audiences with an interest in purchases related to a content category.
